# Intuition
We can use sliding window for k > 0, for k < 0 we can reverse input and calculated outout.

# Approach
For k > 0, we can start by calculating first value with index 0, and sum from 1 to k.
Next we need to update n numbers, on each step we remove i + 1, element from the sum and add, k + i + 1 element to it. Use % of n to ensure data is read from ring buffer.
For case when k < 0 we need to reverse input and output.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> decrypt(vector<int>& code, int k) {
        const int n = code.size();

        vector<int> result(n, 0);
        if (k == 0) {
            return result;
        }

        bool rr = false;
        if (k < 0) {
            reverse(code.begin(), code.end());
            k = -k;
            rr = true;
        }

        int sum = 0;
        for (int i = 1;i <= k;i ++) {
            sum += code[i];
        }

        int j = (k + 1) % n;
        for (int i = 0;i < code.size();i ++) {
            result[i] = sum;
            sum -= code[(i + 1) % n];
            sum += code[j % n];
            j ++;
        }

        if (rr) {
            reverse(result.begin(), result.end());
        }

        return result;
    }
};
```

