# Intuition
The problem clearly deals with an array and sub-array with a window size of k.
# Approach
3 cases:
 1. k==0 return res(output array) as it is with all 0s
 2. k>0 - we form a window of size k with pointers i and j, and move till i!=n-1 to ensure we calc the sum for each element. 
Element to be updated given by i-1
 3. k>0 - we form a window of size k with pointers i and j, and move till i!=n-1 to ensure we calc the sum for each element. Element to be updated given by (j+1)%array.size()

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N)
- Space complexity:
O(1) - excluding the output array
# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> decrypt(vector<int>& v, int k) {

