solutions.content:
This is classic DP problem. 
```
Let nda[i] denote number of deletions for sub-string[0:i] such that it is ending at 'a'
Let ndb[i] denote number of deletions for sub-string[0:i] such that it is ending at 'b'
```

Now loop over each char of str
```
	case 'a'
		nda[i] = nda[i-1]   //No deletions required 
		ndb[i] = ndb[i-1] + 1  // 1 deletion required
		break;
	case 'b'
		ndb[i] = min(nda[i-1], ndb[i-1]) // previous sub-string doesnt matter, it can be 'aa' or 'bb' or 'ab'
		nda[i] = nda[i-1] + 1 // 1 deletion required
```
Now simply return Min of nda[last], ndb[last]
Dry Run:
____aababbab
nda 00112334
ndb 11011122

```
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumDeletions(string s) {
        vector<int>nda(s.size()+1,0);
        vector<int>ndb(s.size()+1,0);
        int i=1;
        for(char ch:s){
            if(ch=='a'){
                ndb[i] = ndb[i-1] + 1;
                nda[i] = nda[i-1] + 0;
            }
            else{
                ndb[i] = min(ndb[i-1],nda[i-1]);
                nda[i] = nda[i-1] + 1;
            }
            i++;
        }
        return min(ndb[s.size()],nda[s.size()]);
    }
};
