I contrast to counting number of characters to delete, I count characters that I can keep in a balanced string that is subsequence of the whole string and calculate number of chars to delete by extracting it from the total string length. `lena` and `lenb` are lengths of the longest subsequences ending with `a` or `b` respectively. 
- `a` can be appended only to subsequence ending with `a`, so the length of new subsequence ending with newly added `a` is `lena + 1`.
- `b` can be appended both to subsequence ending with `a` or `b` so the length of new subsequence will be `max(lena, lenb) + 1`.
