**Key points to understand the solution.**
1. I have taken all variables which will be commonly used by all recursion calls commonly.
2. I have thought of two exit calls that are possible.
    a. First is when my currentNode is equal to my valueToReach value;
	b. If my currNode reaches >6000 ( max of a + max of b + max of c, got the each value from constraint as 2000),         I will simply return.
3. Now for understanding that when to mark a node as visited, consider the following diagram.
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/056e01e4-b28b-4254-91d5-150509aff64c_1634463686.869404.jpeg)
4. There are two possibilities to reach from currNode - a ->currNode OR currNode + b -> currNode.
5. If we consider reaching to currNode from possibility 1, then there are two children possible currNode + a and currNode -b.
6. If we consider reaching to currNode from possibility 2, then there is one child possible i.e currNode -b.
7. If we mark currNode as visited because of possibility 2, then we will miss the one child of which will be currNode + a.
8. So we will always mark currNode as visited if we are taking a forward step from currNode - a or when previousSetp.equals("forward").




