solutions.content:
There are 'n' number of  (key, value) pair provided in random order. First, we need to sort the "values" into a String array, based on their respective 'keys' as index of the array. The question asks us to return **longest possible contiguous subarray from the pointer position, during every iteration of insertion of value into the array.**

Lets say, n=5, and the (Key, Value) pairs are (3,"c") (1,"a") (2,"b") (5,"e") (4,"d"). 
Lets declare a pointer variable ptr=1;     (but while coding, you have to consider 'zero based indexing' for the string array arr[ ]. So ptr=0; ) 

Lets **declare an array** of Strings, arr[ ], of size 'n'. (This is done in **public OrderedStream(int n)**)

Initially the array is filled with null, ( *Bold part of the array is where ptr is pointing* )
arr = | **null** | null | null | null | null |   (ptr=1)

***Iteration 1 :*** (3,"c") is passed to  public List<String> insert(int idKey, String value), ptr is at position 1 of the array.

arr = | **null** | null | "c" | null | null |     =====> pointer is a null, so do nothing. return [ ]

***Iteration 2:*** insert (1,"a")
arr = | **"a"** | null | "c" | null | null |     =====> pointer is not a null,  chunk = "a" , so move the pointer ptr forward, check the next position arr[1] for a value.
arr = | "a" | **null** | "c" | null | null |     =====> But, arr[1] is null, so "a" is the longest chunk of subarray that exists at this point of time. So, return chunk = ["a"] 


***Iteration 3:*** insert (2,"b")
arr = | "a" | **"b"** | "c" | null | null |  =====> pointer is not null, so, chunk = "b". Move the pointer to next position 3, 
arr = | "a" | "b" | **"c"** | null | null |  =====>pointer is not null, so add "c" to the chunk, chunk =" b+ c", move the pointer to 4, value at 4 is null. So return the chunk ["b","c"]

***Iteration 4:*** insert (5,"e")
arr = | "a" | "b" | "c" | **null**  | "e" |                 =====>pointer is null, so do nothing. return [ ]

***Iteration 5:*** insert (4,"d")
arr = | "a" | "b" | "c" | **"d"** | "e" |       =====>pointer is not null, so chunk = "d", pointer moves to position 5.
arr = | "a" | "b" | "c" | "d" | **"e"** |       =====>pointer is not null so chunk = "d" + "e" pointer moves to 6.

6 is greater than length of array. So return chunk ["d" , "e" ] .


