Even though the description may not be entirely clear, paying close attention to the attached GIF will help.

1) A pointer starts at 0-th position (0-based)
2) String data is inserted at K-th position (idKey minus 1)
3) Try to move pointer all the way to right if locations are filled

```
class OrderedStream {
    String[] values; //For index-wise data insertion
    int ptr = 0; //Starting position of pointer

    public OrderedStream(int n) {
        values = new String[n];
    }

    public List<String> insert(int idKey, String value) {
        List<String> output = new ArrayList();
        values[idKey - 1] = value;
		//While values[ptr] is filled, forward ptr
        while (ptr < values.length && values[ptr] != null) {
            output.add(values[ptr++]);
        }
        return output;
    }
}
```

