# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Just need to check both strings must have same elements and the frequencies of those must be same as frequency in other word. It need not be the same element frequency but what matters the numbers.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Just need to check both strings must have same elements and the frequencies of those must be same as frequency in other word. It need not be the same element frequency but what matters the numbers.
Example:
word1="aaabbc"
word2="cccbba"
word1_______word2
a->3________a->1
b->2________b->2
c->1________c->3
word1_______word2
{a,b,c}_________{a,b,c}
{3,2,1}________{1,2,3}->{3,2,1}
since the elements are same and frequency numbers are same return true else false.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(NLogN)$$
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(N)$$
# Code
