        public boolean closeStrings(String word1, String word2) {    

        if(word1.length()!=word2.length())return false;   

        //initialize two arrays with 26 spots ,each index representing each letter of the alphabet.
        // Default: value present on each index is 0 ,representing the occurence of each letter

        int a[]=new int[26];
        int b[]=new int[26];

        //we will loop throgh each letter int word1 and add one to it's corresponding index.
        //If the letter is 'c', then char will be 99-97=2,and we add 1 to arr[2]

        for(Character ch:word1.toCharArray())a[ch-'a']++;
        for(Character ch:word2.toCharArray())b[ch-'a']++;

        /**here we will loop  through each index in both arrays and if one array has no occurences of a 
        letter and the other array does have this letter, then we can return false because there would 
        be no way to perform the given operation and get the correct result.
        word1='ab' , word2='ac', there is no way for these two strings to become 'close' since operation 2 two 
