# Intuition

<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
1.Length of word1 and word2 should be same.
2.Same characters should present in both words.
3.Occurences should be same (not characterwise). Eg- If 'a' is occuring 3 times in word1 then there should be a chacater in word2 which is present in word1 and has occurence 3.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1.If length of both words is not same, return false.
2.Use two unordered maps to store chacaters and their count.
3.Use two min heaps to store values of both maps. (Can use max heap too)
4.Iterate over first map and check 
 (i) key(character of word1) is present in word2, if no return false.If yes, (ii) compare top of both heaps,if not equal, return false,if yes pop top of both heaps and continue..
5.If these 2 conditions satisfies for single traversal of map,return true

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
-Overall traversal will take length of word complexity and for searching in map will take o(1) assuming average case. So overall complexity is o(3 * len(word1)) + o(2 * len(word2))
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
-Used 2 maps and 2 heaps so complexity is o(2 * len(word1)) + o(2 * len(word2))

