Physically changing the input array using the operation seems tedious so I use a frequency table.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Store the no. of occurrence of each alphabets in the input string in a frequency table for alphabets --> find out if the two input strings have the
same letters --> if they do find the no. of occurrence of the numbers in the "frequency table for alphabets" and store them in the frequency table for NUMBERS
if the two frequency tables for NUMBERS are the same, then two strings are close.
