solutions.content:
Intuition is to make frequency maps of both strings.
Keeping word1 as the target.
Since Condition 1 allows swaps , hence both arrays can reach a sorted position(therefore no need to actually sort) .
Once in sorted form all we need to do is check frequency of each character in both words.
If they equal nothing to do move forward
If one of them is 0 and other is non zero answer will always be false as this means character is missing from one of the words.
If they are different. We iterate over the freq2 map in search whther there is another character with freq same as that of word1 character.If found we swap and then move forward.
Now if they were ' close ' freq of each character would be same.

```
class Solution {
    public boolean closeStrings(String word1, String word2) {
        if(word1.length() != word2.length())    return false;

        int[] freq1 = new int[26];
        int[] freq2 = new int[26];
        for(int i=0;i<word1.length();i++){
            freq1[word1.charAt(i)-'a']++;
            freq2[word2.charAt(i)-'a']++;
        }

        for(int i=0;i<26;i++){
            if(freq1[i] == freq2[i])    continue;
            if(freq1[i] == 0 || freq2[i] == 0) return false;

            for(int j=i+1;j<26;j++){
                if(freq2[i] != freq2[j] && freq2[j]  == freq1[i]){
                    int temp = freq2[i];
                    freq2[i] = freq2[j];
                    freq2[j] = temp;
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
        for(int i=0;i<26;i++)
            if(freq1[i] != freq2[i])    return false;
        return true;



    }
}
```

